{{Infobox coat of arms |name = Coat of arms of Ecuador |image = Coat of arms of Ecuador.svg |image_width = 250 |middle = |middle_width = |middle_caption = |lesser = |lesser_width = |lesser_caption = |armiger = [[Republic of Ecuador]] |year_adopted = 31 October 1900 |crest = [[Andean condor]] |torse = None |shield = A landscape consisting of the Guayas River originating from the base of the Chimborazo volcano, on the river a representation of the steamboat 'Guayas' In chief a bend enarched Charged with Inti in splendor and astrological signs |supporters = Two national flags of Ecuador on either side proper |compartment = A Fasces Proper |motto = None |orders = None |other_elements = |earlier_versions = |use = }}
'''The coat of arms of [[Ecuador]]''' (Spanish: ''Escudo de armas del Ecuador'') in its current form was established in 1900 based on an older version of 1845.
==Blazon== In the background of the oval [[Escutcheon (heraldry)|shield]] is the volcano [[Chimborazo (volcano)|Chimborazo]], while the river originating from its base represents the [[Guayas River|Guayas]]. They both symbolize the beauty and wealth of the respective regions (Sierra or Costa). The ship on the river is named ''Guayas'' as well. In 1841 it was built in [[Guayaquil]] and was the first riverine steamship built on the South American west coast; instead of a mast it features a [[Caduceus]] representing trade and economy. On top [[Inti]] in form of a golden sun surrounded by the astronomical signs for [[Aries (astrology)|Aries]], [[Taurus (astrology)|Taurus]], [[Gemini (astrology)|Gemini]] and [[Cancer (astrology)|Cancer]] representing the months March to July to symbolize the duration of the [[Marcist Revolution|March Revolution]] of 1845.
The [[condor]] on top of the shield stretches his wings to symbolize power, greatness and strength of Ecuador. The shield is flanked by four [[Flag of Ecuador|flags of Ecuador]]. The laurel on the left represents the victories of the republic.<ref>Other descriptions attribute it to the symbolism of the glory of the heroes of independence.</ref> The palm leaf on the right side is a symbol of the martyrs of the fight for independence and liberty. The [[fasces]] below the shield represents the republican dignity.<ref>{{cite book |last=Minahan |first=James |date=2010 |title=The Complete Guide to National Symbols and Emblems (Vol. 1)|url=http://www.abc-clio.com/ABC-CLIOCorporate/product.aspx?pc=B2180C |location= |publisher=Greenword Press |page=240 |isbn=978-0313344961 |author-link= }}</ref> {{-}}
==History== The shield was introduced after the victory of the liberal revolution of 1845, but then flanked by white-blue-white flags; which were then replaced in the reintroduction of the [[Flag of Ecuador|''Tricolor'']] flags. The coat of arms in its current form was approved by congress on October 31, 1900.
