{{clear}}
==Usage== [[File:0002+Sucres+Ecuador+1944.jpg|thumb|left|2 Sucres in Silver, 1944]] The coat of arms is used by the President, the parliament, the ministries and several other authorities and public institutions. It is part of the flag, and used on many coins and bills of the former currency [[Ecuadorian sucre|Sucre]] and the coins used today, ''Centavos del [[United States dollar|dólar]]'' of Ecuadorian mintage.
