{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Correggio_deposition.jpg | image_size= 380px | title=Lamentation | artist=[[Antonio Allegri|Correggio]] | year=c. 1524 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=157 | width_metric=182 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum=[[Galleria Nazionale di Parma|Galleria Nazionale]], [[Parma]] }}
The '''''Lamentation of Christ''''' (also known as ''Deposition'') is an [[oil painting|oil on canvas]] painting by the Italian Renaissance artist [[Antonio Allegri|Correggio]], dating from around 1524 and housed in the [[Galleria Nazionale di Parma|Galleria Nazionale]] of [[Parma]], [[Italy]].
==History== The work is one of the canvasses commissioned by Parmesan noble Placido Del Bono for a chapel in the church of [[San Giovanni Evangelista, Parma|San Giovanni Evangelista]] in Parma. They are mentioned (although wrongly assigned to the [[Parma Cathedral|city's cathedral]]) by late Renaissance art biographer [[Giorgio Vasari]] in the first edition of his ''Lives'' (1550).
==Description== The work shows the common [[Lamentation of Christ]] theme, with Jesus depicted immediately after his deposition from the cross, surrounded by the people who loved him in life. They include John, who supports a [[Virgin Mary]] shattered by pain, [[Mary Magdalene]] crying at Jesus' feet and, in the background, [[Nicodemus]] with the pincer he used to remove Christ's nails. The composition was studied accurately to be watched from an oblique point of view, from the entrance of the Del Bono chapel in the church of [[San Giovanni Evangelista, Parma|San Giovanni Evangelista]].
==Sources== *{{cite book|last= Adani|first=Giuseppe|year=2007|title=Correggio pittore universale|location=[[Correggio, Emilia-Romagna|Correggio]]|publisher=Silvana Editoriale}} {{commons category|Martyrdom of four saint}}
==External links== *[http://www.correggioarthome.it/SchedaOpera.jsp?idDocumentoArchivio=2516# Page at Correggio Art Home website] {{it icon}}
